In this statement, President Obama expresses his condolences on the passing of Brandon Lepow, who had worked in politics and as a spokesperson for the White House. The President describes Lepow as hardworking, kind, and gracious, and someone any American would be proud to have working on their behalf. Lepow had been battling leukemia, and the President acknowledges the support and visits from his White House colleagues during his treatment. The President and First Lady share their condolences and support with Lepow's family, friends, and his wife, Theresa. The President also reflects on Lepow's impact, stating that he didn't need to be in politics to change the world, as he had made his thirty-two years count.